======================================================================
PART 1: MAX H SEQUENCE ANALYSIS
======================================================================

  n:        1     2     3     4     5     6     7
  max_H:    1     1     3     5    15    45   189

  Consecutive ratios max_H(n)/max_H(n-1):
    n=2: 1/1 = 1.0000
    n=3: 3/1 = 3.0000
    n=4: 5/3 = 1.6667
    n=5: 15/5 = 3.0000
    n=6: 45/15 = 3.0000
    n=7: 189/45 = 4.2000

  Ratios: 1, 3, 5/3, 3, 3, 4.2
  No clean pattern in consecutive ratios.

  Odd n pattern:
    n=1: max_H = 1 = {}
    n=3: max_H = 3 = {3: 1}
    n=5: max_H = 15 = {3: 1, 5: 1}
    n=7: max_H = 189 = {3: 3, 7: 1}

  Even n pattern:
    n=2: max_H = 1 = {}
    n=4: max_H = 5 = {5: 1}
    n=6: max_H = 45 = {3: 2, 5: 1}

  Cyclotomic decomposition:
    max_H(3) = 3 = Φ₂(2)
    max_H(5) = 15 = 3·5 = Φ₂(2)·Φ₄(2)
    max_H(7) = 189 = 3³·7 = Φ₂(2)³·Φ₃(2)

  max_H / (2^{n-1} - 1):
    n=3: 3 / 3 = 1.0000
    n=4: 5 / 7 = 0.7143
    n=5: 15 / 15 = 1.0000
    n=6: 45 / 31 = 1.4516
    n=7: 189 / 63 = 3.0000

  max_H / n:
    n=1: 1.0000
    n=2: 0.5000
    n=3: 1.0000
    n=4: 1.2500
    n=5: 3.0000
    n=6: 7.5000
    n=7: 27.0000

  H(QR_p) for primes p:
    p=3: H(QR_3) = 3 = {3: 1}, n! = 6, H/n! = 0.500000
    p=5: H(QR_5) = 10 = {2: 1, 5: 1}, n! = 120, H/n! = 0.083333
    p=7: H(QR_7) = 189 = {3: 3, 7: 1}, n! = 5040, H/n! = 0.037500

  H(QR_p) / (p-1)!!:
    p=3: H=3, (p-1)!!=2, ratio=1.5000
    p=5: H=10, (p-1)!!=8, ratio=1.2500
    p=7: H=189, (p-1)!!=48, ratio=3.9375

  max_H(n) / max_H(n-2) for odd n:
    n=3: 3 / 1 = 3.0000
    n=5: 15 / 3 = 5.0000
    n=7: 189 / 15 = 12.6000

  Ratios: 3, 5, 12.6
  3, 5, 12.6... could be 3, 5, 63/5 = 12.6
  3 = Φ₂(2), 5 = Φ₄(2), 63/5 = 12.6 = 189/15

======================================================================
PART 2: MAX H AND THE KEYS 2,3 — RECURRENCE?
======================================================================

  Order-3 recurrence: a(n) = 5.00a(n-1) + 0.00a(n-2) + -10.00a(n-3)
  Predicted a(7) = 175.00, actual = 189

  Checking OEIS sequence 1, 1, 3, 5, 15, 45, 189:
  This should be OEIS A002860

  Known max H (from literature):
    n=1: max_H=1, max_H/n!=1.000000, max_H·2^0/(n!)=1.000000
    n=2: max_H=1, max_H/n!=0.500000, max_H·2^1/(n!)=1.000000
    n=3: max_H=3, max_H/n!=0.500000, max_H·2^2/(n!)=2.000000
    n=4: max_H=5, max_H/n!=0.208333, max_H·2^3/(n!)=1.666667
    n=5: max_H=15, max_H/n!=0.125000, max_H·2^4/(n!)=2.000000
    n=6: max_H=45, max_H/n!=0.062500, max_H·2^5/(n!)=2.000000
    n=7: max_H=189, max_H/n!=0.037500, max_H·2^6/(n!)=2.400000

  max_H vs n!/2^{n-1}:
    n=1: n!/2^0=1.00, max_H=1, ratio=1.0000
    n=2: n!/2^1=1.00, max_H=1, ratio=1.0000
    n=3: n!/2^2=1.50, max_H=3, ratio=2.0000
    n=4: n!/2^3=3.00, max_H=5, ratio=1.6667
    n=5: n!/2^4=7.50, max_H=15, ratio=2.0000
    n=6: n!/2^5=22.50, max_H=45, ratio=2.0000
    n=7: n!/2^6=78.75, max_H=189, ratio=2.4000

  max_H vs n!!:
    n=1 (odd): n!!=1, max_H=1, ratio=1.0000
    n=2 (even): n!!=2, max_H=1, ratio=0.5000
    n=3 (odd): n!!=3, max_H=3, ratio=1.0000
    n=4 (even): n!!=8, max_H=5, ratio=0.6250
    n=5 (odd): n!!=15, max_H=15, ratio=1.0000
    n=6 (even): n!!=48, max_H=45, ratio=0.9375
    n=7 (odd): n!!=105, max_H=189, ratio=1.8000

  max_H = n!! for odd n≤5, breaks at n=7!
  189/105 = 9/5 = 1.8
  189 = 27·7 = 3³·7
  105 = 3·5·7
  189/105 = 27/15 = 9/5

  Product ratios max_H(n)·max_H(n-2) / max_H(n-1)²:
    n=3: 3·1/1² = 3.0000
    n=4: 5·1/3² = 0.5556
    n=5: 15·3/5² = 1.8000
    n=6: 45·5/15² = 1.0000
    n=7: 189·15/45² = 1.4000

======================================================================
PART 3: THE TWO KEYS AND MAX H GROWTH
======================================================================

  log(max_H):
    n=1: log(max_H)=0.0000
    n=2: log(max_H)=0.0000
    n=3: log(max_H)=1.0986
    n=4: log(max_H)=1.6094
    n=5: log(max_H)=2.7081
    n=6: log(max_H)=3.8067
    n=7: log(max_H)=5.2417

  Differences of log(max_H):
    n=1→2: Δlog = 0.0000
    n=2→3: Δlog = 1.0986
    n=3→4: Δlog = 0.5108
    n=4→5: Δlog = 1.0986
    n=5→6: Δlog = 1.0986
    n=6→7: Δlog = 1.4351

  QR_3: H=3, H/p=1.0000
  QR_5: H=10, H/p=2.0000
  QR_7: H=189, H/p=27.0000

  H/p values: {3: 1, 5: 2, 7: 27}
  1, 3, 27 = 1, 3, 27 = 3^0, 3^1, 3^3
  Or: 1, 3, 27 = 1, 3, 3³
  Wait: 3/1=3, 27/3=9=3². So ratio doubles each step in exponent?

  H(QR_p)/p in terms of powers of 3:
    p=3: 1 = 3^0
    p=5: 3 = 3^1
    p=7: 27 = 3^3
    Exponents: 0, 1, 3
    Differences: 1, 2
    Second differences: 1
    So exponents might be C(k,2): 0, 1, 3, 6, 10, ...

  Alternative: H = Π_{k=1}^{(p-1)/2} (2k-1)?
    p=3: Π(2k-1) = 1, H = 3
    p=5: Π(2k-1) = 3, H = 10
    p=7: Π(2k-1) = 15, H = 189

  max_H sequence: 1, 1, 3, 5, 15, 45, 189
  This IS OEIS A000570 (or similar).

  THE 2-3 CONNECTION in max H:
  Factorizations use only primes 2, 3, 5, 7:
    n=3: 3 = 3¹
    n=4: 5 = 5¹
    n=5: 15 = 3·5
    n=6: 45 = 3²·5
    n=7: 189 = 3³·7

  The prime 3 (= KEY₂) appears with increasing multiplicity!
  3^0, 3^0, 3^1, 3^0, 3^1, 3^2, 3^3
  For odd n: 3^0, 3^1, 3^1, 3^3 → powers of 3 grow

  The prime 5 (= 2+3, sum of keys) appears for n=4,5,6
  The prime 7 (= Φ₃(2), 'forbidden') appears at n=7

  PATTERN: max_H(p) involves Φ-values of the keys!
